## How the AI Query Works (RAG Pipeline)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant API as Express API
    participant DB as SQLite
    participant EMB as Gemini Embeddings
    participant LLM as Gemini 2.5 Flash

    U->>API: POST /brain/query { "query": "React hooks?" }
    API->>DB: Fetch all user's embeddings
    API->>EMB: Generate query embedding
    API->>API: Cosine similarity ranking
    API->>API: Filter top-K (score > 0.3)
    API->>LLM: Send query + relevant content context
    LLM-->>API: Generated answer
    API-->>U: { answer, relevantContent[] }
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The vector store uses **SQLite** to store embeddings as JSON arrays. Cosine similarity is computed in-memory. This is perfectly efficient for a personal second brain (thousands of items). For millions of items, swap to a dedicated vector DB like Pinecone or Chroma.

