## Setup — Getting Your Free Gemini API Key

1. Go to **[https://aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com)**
2. Click **"Get API Key"** → Create a key
3. Set it as an environment variable:

```bash
export GEMINI_API_KEY="your-key-here"
npm start
```

> [!TIP]
> Without a Gemini API key, the app still works for all CRUD operations. Embeddings and queries will gracefully degrade with clear error messages.

---

## What Was Fixed from the Original Code

- **`errpr`** typo in auth controller → fixed to `error`
- **Duplicate user signup** — now returns 409 instead of a cryptic error
- **No auth middleware** on content routes — now all content routes are protected
- **Error responses** — unified format with proper HTTP status codes
- **Content controller** — was all stubs, now fully implemented with Zod validation
